oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Edna Rose Hankal
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Tennessee State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Edna Rose Hankal Became the Second Dean of Women at Tennessee State University and Served in That Capacity for Twenty-Three Years, 1935-1950. From 1950-1955 She Was the Residence Director of Hale Hall and From 1955-1958 She Was Head Resident Counselor. Students Dedicated the 1958 Yearbook, The Tennessean to Mrs. Hankal With the Following Remarks, " A Lady In Every Sense Of The Word...Beloved And Respected Near And Far By Young And Not-So-Young Of Both Sexes."
